  <note>
    <title>Sourdough hydration experiments</title>
    <created>20240115T093000Z</created>
    <updated>20240116T100000Z</updated>
    <tag>baking</tag>
    <tag>experiments</tag>
    <note-attributes>
      <author>Test User</author>
    </note-attributes>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Raising hydration from 70% &amp; 75% to 80% gave a much more open crumb.</div><div><br/></div><div>Key learning: at &gt;78% hydration the dough needs coil folds, not stretch &amp; fold.</div></en-note>]]>
    </content>
  </note>
  <note>
    <title>Pasta machine settings</title>
    <created>20240302T181500Z</created>
    <tag>cooking</tag>
    <content>
      <![CDATA[<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><!DOCTYPE en-note SYSTEM "http://xml.evernote.com/pub/enml2.dtd"><en-note><div>Roller setting 6 for tagliatelle &mdash; setting 7 tears the sheet.</div><ul><li>00 flour only</li><li>Rest 30 minutes wrapped</li></ul></en-note>]]>
    </content>
  </note>
